    <introduction>
      <para>Error BE0037: Could not find the path the the MS Help 2 compiler</para>
    </introduction>

    <section>
      <title>Cause</title>
      <content>
        <para>This error occurs when the MS Help 2 compiler could not be
found in the standard location or anywhere in the Program Files folders or
Visual Studio SDK folders on any fixed drive.</para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Solution</title>
      <content>
        <para>The following information can help solve this problem:</para>

<list class="bullet">
  <listItem>Review the <link xlink:href="8c0c97d0-c968-4c15-9fe9-e8f3a443c50a" />
carefully and make sure that you have installed all of the required tools and
have the latest version of each.</listItem>

  <listItem>If all else fails, manually specify the location of the MS Help 2
compiler by entering the path in the <codeInline>HtmlHelp2xCompilerPath</codeInline>
project property.  This usually needs to be done if performing the build on
a build server.</listItem>
</list>

      </content>
    </section>

